Biography

2019-2020

OUTDOOR: Did not compete this season due to COVID-19 pandemic.

INDOOR: Took third in the Long Jump and placed 17th in the 200m with a personal-record of 26:96 at the Mastodon Opener...Placed first in the Triple Jump at the Cedarville Collegiate Invitational...Completed fifth in the Long Jump with a personal best of 5.71m and placed 6th in the Triple Jump with a personal-best of 10.98m at the Horizon League Championships.

2018-19

OUTDOOR: Took fourth at the Kentucky Track & Field Invitational in the triple jump...Had a career best in the long jump at the Horizon League Outdoor Championship at 5.40m (17' 8.75") to garner a fifth place finish.

INDOOR: Had a career best 10.85m (35' 7.5") in the triple jump at the Horizon League Indoor Championship to take 8th.

Prior to NKU: Boasted a personal best of 5.89m (10'4") in the long jump in which she won the New South Wales U18 State Championship (2016) and was the Australian U18 Championship Runner-Up (2016)...In the triple jump, won the Australian U18 National Championship (2016), the New South Wales U18 Championship (2016) and earned the Nick Winter Memorial Award-Aspiring Triple Jumper (2016) while carrying a personal best of 12.33m (40'5.50")...On the track, Leverett holds a personal best of 12.23 in the 100m, an event in which she was the New South Wales State Runner-Up (2016), and a 24.96 PR in the 200m, in which she won the bronze medal at the Australian U18 Junior Championships (2016) and the bronze at the New South Wales State Championships (2016).
